{This chapters deals with one of the most principled alternatives for Black.
White’s pawn structure gets damaged and Black tries to set a blockade rather
than going for the immediate capture of White’s weak pawns. White has
several ways to compensate for its compromised c-pawns. The positions arising
from the lines studied in this chapter are very important for the assessment
of 4.g3.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. g3 c5 5. Nf3 cxd4 6. Nxd4 Ne4 7. Qd3
Bxc3+ {It makes sense to keep the knight on the board as it has a nice post on
c5.} (7... Nxc3 {is understandably less frequently played. As we will see,
Black ends up struggling.} 8. bxc3 Be7 9. Bg2 O-O 10. O-O d6 11. Rd1 a6 12. Ba3
Qc7 13. Qe3 $1 Rd8 (13... Nc6 14. Nxc6 bxc6 15. Rab1 Rb8 16. Rxb8 Qxb8 17. Bxc6
Qc7 {1/2-1/2 (69) Babujian,L (2482)-Bruno,F (2431) Istanbul 2012} 18. Be4 Qxc4
19. Bxd6 $16) (13... Qxc4 14. Nf5 exf5 15. Qxe7 $36) (13... Nd7 14. Nf5 $1) 14.
Rab1 Bf8 (14... Nd7 15. Nxe6 $1 fxe6 16. Qxe6+ Kh8 (16... Kf8 17. Bd5) 17. Qxe7
$18) 15. Nf3 Be7 16. Qb6 Qxb6 17. Rxb6 Nd7 18. Rb2 Nc5 19. Rbd2 Re8 20. Bxc5
dxc5 21. Ne5 $16 {1/2-1/2 (43) Grischuk,A (2747)-Karjakin,S (2776) Monte Carlo
2011}) (7... Nc5 {Not trading on c3 makes little sense.} 8. Qe3 O-O 9. Nc2
Bxc3+ 10. Qxc3 d5 11. Bg2 dxc4 12. Qxc4 Nbd7 13. Be3 $16 {1-0 (34) Legde,G 
(2235)-Diez,G Germany 1995}) 8. bxc3 Nc5 9. Qe3 $5 {[#] White tries to
increase the pressure on the dark squares.} b6 (9... d6 10. Bg2 O-O 11. Ba3
Nba6 12. O-O e5 (12... Qa5 13. Nb5 Bd7 14. Bb4 $1 Nxb4 15. cxb4 Qxb4 16. Rfb1
Qa5 17. Nxd6 Qc7 18. Nxb7 $18 {1-0 (37) Stamenkovic,D (2409)-Cubas,J (2459)
Florianopolis 2015}) 13. Nb5 Qb6 14. Rfd1 Rd8 15. Rd2 Be6 16. Rad1 Qa5 17. Bxc5
Nxc5 18. Nxd6 $18 {1-0 (57) Batsiashvili,N (2310)-Gvetadze,S (2416) Tbilisi
2007}) 10. Bg2 Bb7 11. O-O $5 Bxg2 12. Kxg2 O-O {[%cal Gc1a3,Ge3f3,Gd4b5,Gf1d1,
Gd1d2,Ga1d1] White plans to increase the pressure by means of Ba3, Qf3, Nb5,
Rd2 and Rd1.} ({White would achieve a complete scuccess story after the
careless} 12... Qc7 $2 13. Nf5 O-O (13... Kf8 14. Nxg7 Kxg7 15. Qh6+ Kg8 16.
Bf4 d6) 14. Nxg7 $1 Kxg7 15. Qg5+ Kh8 16. Qf6+ Kg8 17. Bh6) (12... Nc6 13. Nxc6
dxc6 14. Ba3) 13. Ba3 $1 {The right move order.} Nba6 (13... Qc8 14. Qf3 Nba6
15. Rfd1 $14 {1-0 (41) Saric,I (2546)-Sinanovic,M (2339) Biograd na Moru 2018})
14. Rfd1 f5 15. Nb5 $14 *

