{Again we are going to study a very interesting line in which Black underlines
the weakness of White’s doubled (and in some lines tripled) c-pawns. It’s
worth mentioning that Karpov chose this line twice in his 1985 match against
Kasparov, and managed to draw both games. White's chances are better but has
to play the precise move order with 9.Be3 before castling to narrow Black's
options.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. g3 c5 5. Nf3 Nc6 6. Bg2 Ne4 7. Bd2 {
White should be careful as the usual} (7. Qd3 $2 {hands the initiative to
Black.} cxd4 8. Nxd4 Nxc3 9. bxc3 Ne5 10. Qc2 Be7 11. Qb3 O-O 12. Bf4 Qc7 13.
Nb5 Qb8 14. O-O Bc5 15. Rfd1 a6 16. Nd4 d6 17. Rab1 Qc7 18. h3 Rb8 $15 {
0-1 (48) Camarena Gimenez,R (2417)-Gonzalez Garcia,J (2541) Benidorm 2008})
7... Bxc3 8. bxc3 O-O (8... Nxd2 {This line is extremely solid and a bit
passive, as tournament experience shows life is not easy for Black.} 9. Qxd2 d6
10. O-O O-O 11. Rfd1 Qe7 12. Rab1 Rb8 13. dxc5 dxc5 14. Qd6 Qxd6 15. Rxd6 Na5
16. Ne5 b6 17. Rbd1 f6 18. Nc6 Nxc6 19. Bxc6 $16 {1-0 (42) Khalifman,A (2624)
-Chiburdanidze,M (2510) Bazna 2007}) (8... Na5 9. Bf4 d5 (9... O-O 10. dxc5 $14
) 10. cxd5 Nxc3 11. Qc2 Nxd5 (11... cxd4 12. e4 exd5 13. Nxd4 Nxe4 14. Bc7 Qe7
(14... Qf6 15. Bxa5 Qxd4 16. Rd1) 15. Bxa5 (15. Bxe4 Nc6 16. Nxc6 Qxc7 17. Bxd5
O-O) 15... Nxg3+ 16. Kd2 Nxh1 17. Re1 Be6 18. Qa4+ Qd7 19. Nxe6 Qxa4 20. Nc5+
Qe4 21. Nxe4 O-O 22. Nd6 $16) 12. dxc5 Nxf4 13. gxf4 Qc7 14. Rd1 Nc6 15. Rd6
Qa5+ 16. Nd2 $16 {1-0 (52) Ubilava,E (2470)-Ivanov,A Kiev (Ukraine) 1984}) 9.
Be3 $5 ({I'd rather avoid} 9. O-O Na5 10. Bf4 d5 11. cxd5 Nxc3 {as White's
advantage is not ovbious there.}) 9... d5 (9... f5 10. O-O Nxc3 11. Qd3 cxd4
12. Nxd4 Ne4 13. c5 $1 Nxd4 14. Bxd4 b6 15. Bxe4 fxe4 16. Qxe4 Ba6 17. cxb6
axb6 {1/2-1/2 (24) Kasparov,G (2700)-Karpov,A (2720) Moscow (Russia) 1985} 18.
a4 $16) (9... d6 10. O-O $1 Qe7 11. Qd3 f5 12. Rfd1 e5 13. dxe5 dxe5 14. Nh4
$16 {Moisenko - Arencibia, 2003.}) (9... Na5 10. Ne5 $14) 10. dxc5 dxc4 11. Qa4
Nxc3 12. Qxc4 Nd5 13. Bd2 $14 {1/2-1/2 (30) Moiseenko,A (2641)-Iordachescu,V 
(2584) Port Erin 2007} *

[Event "6...Ne4 7.Bd2 Nxd2"]
