19. Bf4 c5 20. Qa5 Nc4 21. Qa6 e5 22. Bxe5 Qxe5 23. Rxe2 Qxc3 24. Ree1 $16 {
White has a pleasant edge as his pawn structure is better and his pieces are
ready to attack the Black trio on the c file. ½-½ (65) Ivanchuk, V (2779)
