$1 e5 21. Bxe5 Nc4 22. Qa6 Qxe5 23. Rxe2 Qxc3 24. Ree1 $16) 20. Be3 Be2 (20...
Bd3 21. e5 $1 {An excellent pawn sacrifice!} Nc4 22. Qa4 Nxe5 23. Qd1 $1 Qxd1 (
23... Qf5 24. Bxc5 $14) 24. Raxd1 c4 25. Bf4 Nc6 26. Rd2 a5 27. Rb2 $14 {
White has more than enough counterplay for the pawn as the b-file is firmly
under his control. ½-½ (42) Mason,I (2168)-Coyne,D ICCF email 2008}) 21. Bf4
Bd3 (21... e5 22. Be3 $1 Bg4 23. Qa6 f6 $2 24. a4 $16 {Black's queenside
