Gc8a6] has been tried sometimes} 11. e4 Ncb4 (11... Ndb4 12. Qe2 Ba6 13. Be3
Na5 14. a3 Nd3 15. b4 $1 Nb3 (15... cxb3 16. Rxd3 c5 17. d5 Bxd3 18. Qxd3 c4 {
1-0 (40) Spasov,S (2315)-Reede,A (1942) ICCF email 2009} 19. Qe2 $16) 16. Rab1
c5 17. dxc5 bxc5 {1/2-1/2 (72) Grandelius,N (2644)-Mareco,S (2650) Linares 2017
} 18. Qa2 $1 $146 cxb4 (18... Bb7 19. Ne5) (18... Qc7 19. b5 Bb7 20. Rxd3) (
18... Nd4 19. b5 Nxf3+ 20. Bxf3 Qa5 21. Bd2) 19. axb4 Bb7 20. Ne1 $14) 12. Qd2
$1 {[%cal Gd2c3] An important detail, White plans to recapture, after ...Nxc3,
with the queen.} Nxc3 13. Qxc3 Bb7 {1/2-1/2 (31) Dragnev,V (2483)-Peralta,F 
(2584) Sitges ESP 2018} 14. Ne5 b5 15. a3 Nc6 16. Nxc6 Bxc6 17. b3 $14 {
White would have a good compensation for the sacrificed pawn.}) 11. e4 (11. Ne5
$5 Nxe5 12. dxe5 c6 13. Ne4 Qc7 14. Nd6 Bxd6 15. exd6 Qxd6 16. Qxc4 $14 {
1/2-1/2 (38) Prohaszka,P (2626)-Bok,B (2639) Saint Louis 2018}) 11... Ndb4 (
11... Nxc3 12. bxc3 b5 13. a4 b4 (13... a6 $2 14. axb5 axb5 15. d5) 14. cxb4
